                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.61 Struma Valley/26: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-11-07T14:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1928—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 7—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. My November 6, 10 a.m. Government has now suggested that Greek loan shall be
                    divided equally between Seligman and Hambro groups, and Seligman representative
                    has agreed to recommend this compromise to his previous note.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
